{"id": "EUVD-2025-22879", "enisaUuid": "209af5ee-ddcd-3409-9438-6030c22a5a08", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niio: backend: fix out-of-bound write\n\nThe buffer is set to 80 character. If a caller write more characters,\ncount is truncated to the max available space in \"simple_write_to_buffer\".\nBut afterwards a string terminator is written to the buffer at offset count\nwithout boundary check. The zero termination is written OUT-OF-BOUND.\n\nAdd a check that the given buffer is smaller then the buffer to prevent.", "datePublished": "2025-07-28T12:30:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T18:31:17", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6eea9f7648ddb9e4903735a1f77cf196c957aa38", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/01e941aa7f5175125df4ac5d3aab099961525602", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/da9374819eb3885636934c1006d450c3cb1a02ed", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38484"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38484"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0bd109ec-ca30-3be6-9809-e5e62a491919", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "199b2463-fb92-3402-bd95-4f614ad42208", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "035b4989211dc1c8626e186d655ae8ca5141bb73 <01e941aa7f5175125df4ac5d3aab099961525602"}, {"id": "20d7f772-2ce4-3fcd-b98c-de3a49a0e98f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fd791c81f410ab1c554686a6f486dc7a176dfe35"}, {"id": "25184de8-6f3f-30e9-89a8-44b61cefc82e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.15"}, {"id": "737e4692-ac57-3523-a22c-af49bdbe9be6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "04271a4d2740f98bbe36f82cd3d74677a839d1eb"}, {"id": "87eaadce-cfab-3f34-a73f-cfb33026dfb1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "888f40b0-8148-3594-be38-94efbb438901", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "df3892e5e861c43d5612728ed259634675b8a71f <6eea9f7648ddb9